==English==
===Etymology===
From English [[colre]], from Old French colre, from Latin [[cholera]], "[[jaundice]]", from Greek [[kholera]], from Greek [[khol]], "[[bile]]"


===Adjective===
'''choleric'''
# Easily becoming [[angry]].
# Showing or expressing [[anger]].

